Oh wow, is this how much i miss my training phases in ns? Hahahah miss my friends and all the sufferings, wait to rush rush to wait moments, all the marches, route march, stairs climb, march to cookhouse, all the training and outfields, ranges, rifle cleaning. Hahaha dang...

Well, everytime people say ns sucks and stuff, I kinda I’ll tell them otherwise cause, everyone is going through it together. Everywhere you go, people are on the same boat as you. You go to the bunks, outfield, wherever. Clean together, suffer together. Haha

I’d say no, cause it’s just not really my kind of environment. To work and be there for my life. But it’s really fun to be in NS (training phases). For muslim trainees, FASTING MONTH’S THE BEST! Damn damn damn. Hahahahahaha

If you were to ask me whether I would relive my ns days. I would say both yes and no. I’d say yes cause of all the brother’s you’ll meet in the company and the things you never thought you’ll ever do or achieve. To tell you the truth ns made me less scared of everything.

It was really a bittersweet memory in NS. Especially in Cougar Company (BMT) and Delta Company (SCS). I can still remember everything like it was just yesterday. Can’t believe that all of us, enlisted 4 years back. Man...

From the pain to the laughter. From strangers to building friendship to brotherhood. Bonded like never before. All the times we shared our punishment, standby area or bed, to checking our items for outfield.
You know. After Watching “Every Singaporean Son” the animated series, it made me think about my ns days. Especially as a trainee and cadet. Some of THE best memories were created there, i swear.
